⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of FFVI
node FF6 · FF6 · ⟦FFVI:FF6:549ab2⟧

WHO   — FFVI — the sixth lineage — the first game-world
WHAT  — Final Fantasy VI — the ensemble JRPG where magic and machine go to war, the villain wins, and fourteen scattered souls gather to take a ruined world back.
WHERE — the steam-and-magic world of the Gestahlian Empire — Narshe, Figaro, Doma, the Esper world; the World of Balance and the World of Ruin  Framework inputs: Final Fantasy VI; the Espers and Magitek; the World of Balance and Ruin; Uematsu's score  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Universe David 0)
WHY   — The Empire drained the Espers to build its Magitek, a mad god broke the world — and the survivors chose to rebuild it anyway.
HOW   — Crystallized from Final Fantasy VI (Super Famicom, 1994), released in North America as Final Fantasy III.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  The Empire built its power on drained magic and a god of ruin broke the world — yet the survivors chose to rebuild it.

